main_text: ğŸ™‹ Would you try these?!These chickpea fritters come together quickly and easily with a few simple ingredients. Serve as an appetizer or main and they are great for meal prep!....By @feelgoodfoodieThey can be made ahead of time and are great for meal prep! Easily made gluten free or dairy free by swapping a few ingredients!INGREDIENTS* 1 15-ounce canned chickpeas rinsed drained* Â¼ cup flour of choice* Â¼ cup grated or shredded parmesan cheese or nutritional yeast* 1 tablespoon chopped parsley* 1 teaspoon cumin* Â½ teaspoon garlic powder* Â½ teaspoon salt* Â¼ teaspoon black pepper* 2 tablespoons water* 2 tablespoons oil of choice* tahini sauce for servingğŸ‘©â€ğŸ³ Instructions1. In a medium bowl combine the chickpeas all purpose flour parmesan cheese fresh herbs cumin garlic powder salt and pepper. Add two tablespoons of water and use a fork or masher to combine the ingredients until they are well blended.2. Divide the mixture into 6 equal parts and form into thin patties.3. In a large pan heat the oil until it's shimmering. Then add the chickpea fritters and cook until browned and fully cooked through about 2-4 minutes per side.4. Place on a plate lined with a paper towel to absorb any excess oil then serve with tahini sauce or any other sauce of choice.#chickpeas #snacks #snack #appetizers #appetizer #veggies #chickpea #healthyrecipes #healthyrecipe #snacking

* 1 15-ounce canned chickpeas rinsed  drained
* Â¼ cup flour of choice
* Â¼ cup grated or shredded parmesan cheese or nutritional yeast
* 1 tablespoon chopped parsley
* 1 teaspoon cumin
* Â½ teaspoon garlic powder
* Â½ teaspoon salt
* Â¼ teaspoon black pepper
* 2 tablespoons water
* 2 tablespoons oil of choice
* tahini sauce for serving

ğŸ‘©â€ğŸ³ Instructions
1. In a medium bowl  combine the chickpeas  all purpose flour  parmesan cheese  fresh herbs  cumin  garlic powder  salt and pepper. Add two tablespoons of water and use a fork or masher to combine the ingredients until they are well blended.
2. Divide the mixture into 6 equal parts and form into thin patties.
3. In a large pan  heat the oil until it's shimmering. Then add the chickpea fritters and cook until browned and fully cooked through  about 2-4 minutes per side.
4. Place on a plate lined with a paper towel to absorb any excess oil  then serve with tahini sauce or any other sauce of choice.

{"1": {"comment_id": "themediterraneanhousewife"  "comment_text": "Nourishing lentil soup - Faki (Ï†Î±ÎºÎ®). When you need something light but filling x â£
.â£
.â£
.â£Make yourself a bowl of Faki tonight:
2/3 cup green lentils
1 diced carrot
1 diced red onion
3 cloves garlic diced
1 bay leaf
Salt/ pepper to taste
One stall celery - chopped.
A few cups of water.
Olive oil.
Tomato paste - 1 tbsp
Rinse the lentils
Add everything into a pot except the lentils  tomato paste and the water.
Fry till the garlic is cooked and golden.
Add lentils and stir
Add enough water to cover everything - 2 to 3 cups boiled water.
Add the tomato paste
Bring to a boil
Dinner for 30 minutes.
Taste and test as you go.
I eat my lentil soup with crusty bread and vinegar. Enjoy xx

main_text: What are the benefits of chickpeas? In addition to being a great source of fiber and protein chickpeas contain a lot more uses. I toasted some jalapeÃ±o cheddar toast to go with it but it also works with any kind of bread rice or grain. Highly recommend this recipe!Ingredientsâ€¢2 Tbsp olive oil â€¢2 cloves garlic â€¢1 tsp grated fresh gingerâ€¢1 yellow onion â€¢1 Tbsp curry powder â€¢1 Tbsp smoked paprika â€¢pinch crushed red pepper â€¢1 tbsp fresh tarragon rippedâ€¢1 tsp dried rosemaryâ€¢2 russet potatoes (1.75-2 lbs total) â€¢1 15oz. can chickpeas â€¢4 cups vegetable brothInstructionsâ€¢Finely dice the onion mince the garlic and grate the ginger. Add the onion garlic and ginger to a large soup pot with the olive oil and sautÃ© over medium heat until the onions are soft and transparent.â€¢Add the curry powder smoked paprika tarragon rosemary and red pepper flakes to the pot and continue to stir and cook for 1-2 minutes more to toast the spices.â€¢While the onion garlic and ginger are sautÃ©ing peel the potatoes and cut them into 1-inch cubes. Drain the chickpeas. â€¢Once the spices are toasted add the potatoes and chickpeas to the pot. â€¢1 tsp dried rosemary
â€¢2 russet potatoes (1.75-2 lbs total) 
â€¢1 15oz. can chickpeas 
â€¢4 cups vegetable broth

Instructions
â€¢Finely dice the onion  mince the garlic  and grate the ginger. Add the onion  garlic  and ginger to a large soup pot with the olive oil and sautÃ© over medium heat until the onions are soft and transparent.

â€¢Add the curry powder  smoked paprika  tarragon  rosemary  and red pepper flakes to the pot and continue to stir and cook for 1-2 minutes more to toast the spices.

â€¢While the onion  garlic  and ginger are sautÃ©ing  peel the potatoes and cut them into 1-inch cubes. Drain the chickpeas. 

â€¢Once the spices are toasted  add the potatoes  and chickpeas to the pot. Pour the vegetable broth over top  then stir until everything is combined.

â€¢Place a lid on the pot  turn the heat up to medium-high  and allow it to come to a boil. Once boiling  turn the heat down to low and allow the soup to simmer with the lid in place for 45 minutes  stirring occasionally.

â€¢Taste the soup and adjust the salt or other spices if desired. Serve!

main_text: Aquafaba (vegan) MeringueMy vegan friends and friends with egg allergiesâ€¦ or friends who just love meringue - this is a good one. Following my previous post making hummus and chickpea water - Iâ€™ve heard that chickpea water also known as aquafaba is an alternative to egg white when my daughter had an egg allergy. Sheâ€™s actually outgrown her allergy now but I was quite excited to try make these aquafaba meringues. You can find a recipe on cookidoo to make in your Thermomix.I had my doubts as I was making these as I can definitely still smell chickpea up until the point I was putting them into the oven and thought it was going to be strange. Somehow the chickpea smell and taste disappears completely when itâ€™s out of the oven.I had some frozen raspberries which I used to make a purÃ©e to add to the meringue for some extra zing and sweetness and they make them look pretty as well. I used cream of tartar to help stabilise the meringue as I didnâ€™t have lemon juice or white vinegar which was used in the recipe and it worked fine.Iâ€™m pleasantly surprised with the results. The mini meringue kisses are super light crispy and have a gorgeous chewy centre too.They are so moreish - I need to make more of them.#thermomixukandireland #thermomixuk #TM6 #cookidoorecipe #vegan #aquafabameringue #freefrom #eggless #homemade #nowaste #aquafaba #chickpea #bromleymums #pettswoodmums #nowaste
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mamaju_cooks"  "comment_text": "Aquafaba (vegan) Meringue

My vegan friends and friends with egg allergiesâ€¦ or friends who just love meringue - this is a good one. Following my previous post making hummus and chickpea water - Iâ€™ve heard that chickpea water  also known as aquafaba  is an alternative to egg white when my daughter had an egg allergy. Sheâ€™s actually outgrown her allergy now  but I was quite excited to try make these aquafaba meringues. You can find a recipe on cookidoo to make in your Thermomix.

I had my doubts as I was making these as I can definitely still smell chickpea up until the point I was putting them into the oven and thought it was going to be strange. Somehow  the chickpea smell and taste disappears completely when itâ€™s out of the oven.

I had some frozen raspberries which I used to make a purÃ©e to add to the meringue for some extra zing and sweetness  and they make them look pretty as well. I used cream of tartar to help stabilise the meringue as I didnâ€™t have lemon juice or white vinegar which was used in the recipe and it worked fine.

main_text: Sunday Snack: Do you like hummus? Do you find them hard to digest?Making hummus is a great high protein snack and is very easy to make.It is simply a case of blending chickpeas lemon juice olive oil tahini garlic salt etc in a blender.However there are a few tricks to make it tastier and easier to digest.1. Toast some sesame seeds for a richer and fuller flavour2. Add cumin paprika and cayenne for more of a spice richness and to help digestion.3. Roast your garlic prior for a more pungent garlic flavour and for a great antioxidant.4. Use sprouted chickpeas rather than tinned chickpeas as they are easier to digest and higher in nutrients.This is a photo of some hummus a made for a health retreat a little while ago with a spiral of saffron ğŸ˜ŠYummy ğŸ˜#sundaysnack #hummus #hummusrecipe #chickpea #digestion #garlic #ketodiet #veganfood #vegetarian #glutenfree #wheatfree #dairyfree #naturalchef #nutritionist #healthcoach #adidibite #didi #tipsdiet #foodhacks #protein #sprouted
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "a_didi_bite"  "comment_text": "Sunday Snack: Do you like hummus? Do you find them hard to digest?

Making hummus is a great high protein snack and is very easy to make.

It is simply a case of blending chickpeas  lemon juice  olive oil  tahini  garlic  salt etc in a blender.

However there are a few tricks to make it tastier and easier to digest.
1. Toast some sesame seeds for a richer and fuller flavour
2. Add cumin  paprika and cayenne for more of a spice richness and to help digestion.
3. Roast your garlic prior for a more pungent garlic flavour and for a great antioxidant.
4. Use sprouted chickpeas rather than tinned chickpeas as they are easier to digest and higher in nutrients.

This is a photo of some hummus a made for a health retreat a little while ago with a spiral of saffron ğŸ˜Š

Yummy ğŸ˜

{"1": {"comment_id": "feastwithsafiya"  "comment_text": "Got chickpeas and potatoes on hand? Make this quick and easy Indian Chickpea & Potato salad. Delicious  refreshing  and out of this world delicious ğŸ˜‹.

-2 cups boiled desi chickpeas
-1 cup boiled chopped potatoes
-1/3 cup diced onion
-1/2 cup diced tomato
-1/4 cup tamarind chutney
-1/4 cup chopped cilantro
-2 tbsp diced green chili(like Thai  Serrano  or jalapeno)
-1 tsp Kashmiri chili powder  1/2 tsp for mildly spicy
-1/2 tsp roasted cumin powder
-1/2 tsp amchur powder or chaat masala  1 tsp for a good desi kick
-1 tsp salt (Himalayan pink or black salt)

1. Combine all the ingredients in a large prep bowl. Toss everything well until well combined.
2. Serve it as a salad  side dish  or snack.

Safiya
